		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Magician Leveling to 20</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:balebe@hotmail.com">Infestation</a> | 
		            4/6/2000 4:29:32 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Well I have read most of the Mage links in this archive and have wondered why people have taken so long to level, currently I am a level 20 mage and have about 5 days on my played record so here goes for a quick and easy leveling guide or at least how I did it. Deciding that my life was rather dull and boring being a Good human cleric, I decided to play an evil class, henceforth I am a DE. From level 1-2 I fought snakes, black wolves and decaying skellys. Level 3-5 I fought ONLY spiderlings and fire beetles. Level 6-9 I fought skeletons try to pick them individually multiple ones can be a pain and costly in the purse for losing pets. From level 10-14 fight either caimens in Oasis they will even take you to 16...fight crocs if you wish at 14 but not before they hit hard even if a blue con. At level 14-16 I traveled back to Neriak to the Third Gate, to a lovely little inn called the Maiden's Fancy...there you find 4 npc's that are ripe for the fighting.  Upstairs you will find Molon whom is a thief and hits hard but your pet and yourself can take him Ebon mask is the only bad faction you take...Also Ratraz the troll is there...if you are an agnostic mage dont fight him for then you cannot repair your faction unless you go to SRO or OOT...if you want to fight Ratraz do in a pair or fight at level 19...he drops warmaul (sells for 4-5p a pop) however he hurts your guard and shopkeeper faction in Neriak...buy 20 red wine from Cecile at the bar and give to the man behind the door in the Library cannot remember his name (sorry) but only one door in the library anyways;) Give in units of 5 and fill up the 4 slots of wine...Now you can kill ratraz 2 more times before you do that again....great exp and good money for spells;) Downstairs you find a monk behind a door named Tayla Ironforge she is black at 15 and with your pet you can destroy her...cruddy loot but good exp...when you hit level 18+ you can now take Spice another thief downstairs she will con yellow..she hits hard so I would recommend fire shield on yourself and being full mana before you take her...use either wind or water summoned pet for this...she is bad loot but Great exp for a level 18-20....All of these NPCS will take you to 20 they are safe and close to home...bind outside the inn in the third gate...At level 20 I would suggest you now do caverns and dungeons...closest ones to home are Najena and Befallen...Do Najena with a group of about 3-4 others level 20 also...and you can do pretty much everything cept for Drelzna...wait till level 26+ for her...Befallen...again with a group of 3-4 you can take pretty much everything in there...only thing I dont like about Befallen besides the fact that those round earred buggers leave dark elf parts lying around as some form of sick humor is that the only good loot outta there is Demask armor, which has the same AC as silk armor....Najena has much better loot Large Bronze from Ogre captain Runed circlet components from Najena herself and from Parlone, Journeyman Boot components from Najena TT whips, the odd PBB( polished bone bracer) and of course Stiletto of the Bloodclaw from Drelzna GREAT necro and thief weapon...SKs can also use but they prefer great 2 handed weapons like the Dark Reaver...that about sums it up to get ya to level 20...currently spending most of my time researching and will drop off a page on how to's/ and where to finds... Take care and stay evil (grin?<BR>
<BR>
   Infestation
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
